This paper focuses on developing a method for predicting human behavior in the context of human-robot collaboration, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces a nonlinear recursive least square parameter adaptation algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques such as multi-task learning (cs.AI) and parameter adaptation (cs.LG). The method involves analyzing human trajectories, which can be considered a computer vision problem (cs.CV). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of creating safe and efficient human-robot collaboration, which is a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) concern.
